between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
SENATE BILL No. 208
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
insurance.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 5-10-8-2.3 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
3 1, 2026]: Sec. 2.3. (a) This section applies to a policy that is issued,
4 delivered, amended, or renewed after June 30, 2026.
5 (b) A group health insurance program established under section
6 2.2 of this chapter for firefighters must provide coverage for the
7 screening of:
8 (1) colon cancer;
9 (2) lung cancer;
10 (3) bladder cancer;
11 (4) oral cancer;
12 (5) thyroid cancer;
13 (6) skin cancer;
14 (7) blood cancer;
15 (8) breast cancer;
16 (9) cervical cancer;
17 (10) testicular cancer;
2026 IN 208—LS 6816/DI 141

2
1 (11) prostate cancer; and
2 (12) any other form of cancer that is generally recognized as
3 having a higher risk of occurrence in a person who performs
4 firefighting services.
5 (c) Except as provided in subsection (d), the coverage required
6 by this section may not be subject to any copayment, deductible,
7 coinsurance, or other cost sharing requirement.
8 (d) If a group health insurance program established under
9 section 2.2 of this chapter for firefighters is offered as a qualifying
10 high deductible health plan for a health savings account, the group
11 health insurance program shall establish cost sharing for the
12 coverage under this section at the minimum level necessary to
13 preserve the insured's ability to claim tax exempt contributions
14 and withdrawal from the insured's health savings account under
15 26 U.S.C. 223.
16 SECTION 2. IC 5-10-8-2.4 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
17 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
18 1, 2026]: Sec. 2.4. (a) As used in this section, "firefighter" means a
19 full-time firefighter.
20 (b) A local unit public employer shall provide cancer insurance
21 for:
22 (1) active firefighters;
23 (2) retired firefighters; and
24 (3) firefighters who are receiving disability benefits under
25 IC 36-8-7 or IC 36-8-8.
26 (c) A local unit public employer shall provide cancer insurance
27 under subsection (b) through one (1) of the following methods:
28 (1) By purchasing policies of group insurance.
29 (2) By establishing self-insurance programs.
30 (3) If the board of trustees of INPRS provides cancer
31 insurance under IC 5-10.5-4-2(a)(18), by electing to provide
32 the coverage through a policy adopted by the board of
33 trustees of INPRS.
34 (d) A local unit public employer may pay a part of the cost of
35 cancer insurance for:
36 (1) active firefighters;
37 (2) retired firefighters; and
38 (3) firefighters who are receiving disability benefits under
39 IC 36-8-7 or IC 36-8-8.
40 (e) A local unit public employer may not cancel an insurance
41 contract under this section during the policy term of the contract.
